附加记录：    

Yeah, see this is where you lost me for good. The fact that the conclusion of the SCP, the part where it all falls into place, is shoved in a tale that is completely separate from this piece is enough for my downvote alone. The era from which such a practice is deemed acceptable has long since passed. The entire point of an SCP is to tell a complete narrative within the restrictions of the format. I shouldn't have to go to a completely different Wikidot site page (since the old addenda has now been localized here) to find your ending. This article doesn't stand on its own two feet.





